\begin{definition}[Taylor morphism] We write  $\mathfrak R_{\mathrm{Taylor},d/dx}$ for the homomorphism from $(\mathcal D,+,\times)$ to $(\Frec,\oplus,\otimes)$ defined by \[
  \mathfrak R_{\mathrm{Taylor},d/dx} (x)=(1,S_n),\qquad\mathfrak R_{\mathrm{Taylor},d/dx}(\partial)=(n S_n,1)
\] and for all $\lambda\in\K$, $\mathfrak R_{\mathrm{Taylor},d/dx}(\lambda)=(\lambda,1)$. \end{definition}

